#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.12:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Caravagga"
msgstr "2. Walking"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Sīlasutta"
msgstr "12. Ethics"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sampannasīlā, bhikkhave, viharatha sampannapātimokkhā, "
"pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvutā viharatha ācāragocarasampannā, aṇumattesu vajjesu "
"bhayadassāvino samādāya sikkhatha sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, live by the ethical precepts and the monastic code. Live "
"restrained in the code of conduct, accomplished in appropriate behavior and "
"means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the slightest flaw, keep the "
"rules you’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an4.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sampannasīlānaṃ vo, bhikkhave, viharataṃ sampannapātimokkhānaṃ "
"pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvutānaṃ viharataṃ ācāragocarasampannānaṃ aṇumattesu "
"vajjesu bhayadassāvīnaṃ samādāya sikkhataṃ sikkhāpadesu, kimassa uttari "
"karaṇīyaṃ?"
msgstr "When you’ve done this, what more is there to do?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:2.1"
msgid ""
"Carato cepi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno abhijjhābyāpādo vigato hoti, thinamiddhaṃ …"
" uddhaccakukkuccaṃ … vicikicchā pahīnā hoti, āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ "
"asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ "
"cittaṃ ekaggaṃ, carampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃbhūto ‘ātāpī ottāpī satataṃ "
"samitaṃ āraddhavīriyo pahitatto’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a mendicant has got rid of desire and ill will while walking, and "
"has given up dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt. "
"Their energy is roused up and unflagging, their mindfulness is established "
"and lucid, their body is tranquil and undisturbed, and their mind is "
"immersed in samādhi. Such a mendicant is said to be ‘keen and prudent, "
"always energetic and determined’ when walking."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:3.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhitassa cepi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno abhijjhābyāpādo vigato hoti, "
"thinamiddhaṃ … uddhaccakukkuccaṃ … vicikicchā pahīnā hoti, āraddhaṃ hoti "
"vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, "
"samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ, ṭhitopi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃbhūto ‘ātāpī "
"ottāpī satataṃ samitaṃ āraddhavīriyo pahitatto’ti vuccati."
msgstr "Suppose a mendicant has got rid of desire and ill will while standing …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:4.1"
msgid ""
"Nisinnassa cepi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno abhijjhābyāpādo vigato hoti, "
"thinamiddhaṃ … uddhaccakukkuccaṃ … vicikicchā pahīnā hoti, āraddhaṃ hoti "
"vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, "
"samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ, nisinnopi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃbhūto ‘ātāpī "
"ottāpī satataṃ samitaṃ āraddhavīriyo pahitatto’ti vuccati."
msgstr "sitting …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:5.1"
msgid ""
"Sayānassa cepi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno jāgarassa abhijjhābyāpādo vigato hoti, "
"thinamiddhaṃ … uddhaccakukkuccaṃ … vicikicchā pahīnā hoti, āraddhaṃ hoti "
"vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, "
"samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ, sayānopi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgaro evaṃbhūto ‘"
"ātāpī ottāpī satataṃ samitaṃ āraddhavīriyo pahitatto’ti vuccatīti."
msgstr ""
"lying down while awake, and has given up dullness and drowsiness, "
"restlessness and remorse, and doubt. Their energy is roused up and "
"unflagging, their mindfulness is established and lucid, their body is "
"tranquil and undisturbed, and their mind is immersed in samādhi. Such a "
"mendicant is said to be ‘keen and prudent, always energetic and determined’ "
"when lying down while awake."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: Yataṃ → yathā (mr)
#. VAR: yataṃ → yathā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.12:6.1"
msgid "Yataṃ care yataṃ tiṭṭhe,"
msgstr "Carefully walking, carefully standing,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Yataṃ → yathā (mr)
#. VAR: yataṃ → yathā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.12:6.2"
msgid "Yataṃ acche yataṃ saye;"
msgstr "carefully sitting, carefully lying;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Yataṃ → yathā (mr)
#. VAR: samiñjaye → sammiñjaye (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.12:6.3"
msgid "Yataṃ samiñjaye bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a mendicant carefully bends their limbs,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Yatamenaṃ → yatameva naṃ (bj) | yatametaṃ (s1-3, km) | yatameva (?)
msgctxt "an4.12:6.4"
msgid "Yatamenaṃ pasāraye."
msgstr "and carefully extends them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:7.1"
msgid "Uddhaṃ tiriyaṃ apācīnaṃ,"
msgstr "Above, below, and all around,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.12:7.2"
msgid "yāvatājagatogati;"
msgstr "as far as the earth extends;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.12:7.3"
msgid "Samavekkhitā ca dhammānaṃ,"
msgstr "they scrutinize the rise and fall"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.12:7.4"
msgid "khandhānaṃ udayabbayaṃ."
msgstr "of phenomena such as the aggregates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.12:8.1"
msgid "Cetosamathasāmīciṃ,"
msgstr "Training in what leads to serenity of heart,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.12:8.2"
msgid "sikkhamānaṃ sadā sataṃ;"
msgstr "always staying mindful;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.12:8.3"
msgid "Satataṃ pahitattoti,"
msgstr "they call such a mendicant"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.12:8.4"
msgid "āhu bhikkhuṃ tathāvidhan”ti."
msgstr "‘always determined’.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.12:8.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
